Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Drain the @Halloumi{250%g}, then cut it into 2cm chunks. Place them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Halve the @Bell Pepper{1} and discard the core and seeds. Chop into 2cm chunks, then pop onto a #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @oil{drizzle}, scatter over half the @Italian Style Herbs{1/2%tsp} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Toss to coat, then roast on the top shelf of your oven until browned and tender, ~{20-25%minutes}.

Meanwhile, pop the @Garlic Clove{2}(unpeeled) into a small piece of #foil{} with a drizzle of oil and scrunch to enclose it.

Halfway through the pepper roasting time, pop the garlic parcel onto the same baking tray and roast until soft, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Meanwhile, remove the halloumi cubes from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the halloumi and fry, turning regularly, until golden brown all over, ~{4-5%minutes}. Transfer to a plate and set the pan aside.

Bring a large #saucepan{} of water to the boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Return the (now empty) frying pan to medium heat. Add the @Finely Chopped Tomatoes with Onion and Garlic{1}, @Vegetable Stock Paste{10%g}, remaining @Italian Style Herbs{1/2%tsp}, @Sugar{1/2%tsp} and @Water for the Sauce{75%ml}.

Season with salt and pepper, then bring to the boil. Lower the heat and gently simmer, stirring occasionally, until thickened, ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once the garlic is roasted, allow it to cool, then cut the end with #scissors{} and squeeze it out of the skin. Mash with the back of a #fork{} and stir into the sauce.

While the sauce simmers, add the @Rigatoni Pasta{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

Once the pepper has roasted, stir it through the thickened sauce along with the fried halloumi.

Add the @Baby Spinach{100%g} to the sauce a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add a splash of water to loosen if it's a little thick. Taste and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Once the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and stir it through the sauce.

Divide the halloumi rigatoni between your #bowls{}. Enjoy!